fields.heading: Combining all my interests into one company. That's what it's all about!
fields.body:
First of all, welcome! I'm quite excited about this new project and have many ideas of where I would like to take it.

First and foremost, Azul Cloud Studio is a website development company. We create websites for small businesses and start-up companies in need of affordable software development. Our sites range from very simple personal websites to full-scale websites with complete authorization systems, social integration, email, complex business logic, advanced and modern website design, advanced database models, and most importantly of all.... MUCH LOVE!

A little about me

I really don't want to focus too much, or at all, on myself. However, I think it's important to know a labout myself so you can fully understand the aspirations of Azul Cloud Studio.

This project is a culmination of my greatest interests and hobbies rolled up into one. I love web development. I love small business. I love Colombia. What happens when you combine those three things? You guessed it, Azul Cloud Studio.

The idea started while I was long-term traveling through South America and after people learned I was a website developer they started asking me if I could develop a website for them. Well... yeah, actually, I could! From then on, piece by piece, I started developing the founding ideas of this company.

I have a lot of interest in small businesses and start-ups. Ever since my college years I've had this interest, and I think I always will. There's something that is just innately more challenging with start-ups than anything else I have ever experienced. It is something that takes more skill, passion, risk, determination and dedication than any run-of-the-mill job.

Getting into web development...

Next up is my passion for web development, which was a late-bloomer in my IT repertoire. In my short 5-year career in the United States, I spent most of my days with Business Intelligence, Database Development and Administration, IT Analysis, Business Process Modeling, and Project Management. I always had a strong interest in web development, but my first manager always told me "You can't do web development, you're not a Computer Science major and you're taking classes for an MBA". As you can probably tell, that is something that has stuck with me.

Before I left my job, I started doing web development in my spare time. All of my spare time. I had plans of traveling so I began development of a travel blog - which turned out to be a great first project. Something that took me about 2 months to develop back then I could now pump out in just a couple days.

With each project I took on, the more I enjoyed web development. Each and every day I am challenged and can see improvement. I love it.

What does Colombia have to do with anything??

I won't go into all the details, but I have a strong interest for Colombia. If you would like to learn more about that, you can read my travel blog at ... But here I'll only be talking about the part that is relavent to Azul Cloud Studio

Colombia has a growing economy. If you think I'm wrong, wait ten years, and then tell me I'm wrong. I'll be waiting! There have been more and more foreign investment into Colombia, and many start-ups that have ... started up. Because of my passion for Colombia, I want to help out. My aspirations in Colombia are not financial, they are intended to help out the business community and help the country develop.

Other than strictly web development, I have other plans in Colombia that are based around training low-income individuals without much opportunity but tons of learning capacity. The people who excel in their trial would be offered employment and worked into the development and maintenance teams.

So there you have it, all of my interests that I have turned into my job. This will be the single most difficult thing I have ever done, but as those close to me know, I am always up to the challenge!
fields.title: About The Founder, Adam

fields.heading: The 4 Pillars of Azul Cloud Studio
fields.body:
I have some clear goals in mind when setting up this venture, and I wouldn't be going at it without having some long-term goals in mind. We will call these the 4 pillars of Azul Cloud Studio, which is a term I just made up on the spot.

Help Startups and Small Business

Develop Deserving People

Improve Colombian Business Environment

Health Client Relationships
